  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      OBJECTIVES:

      I. Evaluate the mechanisms of ultraviolet A-1 light therapy in patients with systemic lupus
      erythematosus and normal controls.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      PROTOCOL OUTLINE:

      Treatment with ultraviolet A-1 light is administered 5 days a week for 6 weeks, at the lowest
      dose or frequency required to maintain a response. The dose and frequency are progressively
      decreased over the next 9 weeks.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
